Web Scrapping of a Wikipedia Page¶

  • Here we are going to perform web scrapping to form a dataframe which consists of the name of countries and their population.

  • Our source of information is:

    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_and_dependencies_by_population

In [1]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

Creating Soup:¶

We are going to use Beautiful Soup python library to do the web scrapping.

In [2]:
url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_and_dependencies_by_population'
source = requests.get(url)
In [3]:
soup = BeautifulSoup(source.text,"html.parser")
In [4]:
soup

<h1 class="firstHeading" id="firstHeading">List of countries and dependencies by population</h1>
<div class="vector-body" id="bodyContent">
<div class="noprint" id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
<div id="contentSub"></div>
<div id="contentSub2"></div>
<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>
<div class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr" id="mw-content-text" lang="en"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Wikipedia list article</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:282px;"><a class="image" href="/wiki/File:World_Population.svg"><img alt="" class="thumbimage" data-file-height="1398" data-file-width="2754" decoding="async" height="142" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/World_Population.svg/280px-World_Population.svg.png" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/World_Population.svg/420px-World_Population.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/World_Population.svg/560px-World_Population.svg.png 2x" width="280"/></a> <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a class="internal" href="/wiki/File:World_Population.svg" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Map of countries and territories by population in 2019 (the darker, the larger the population)</div></div></div>
<p>This is a <b>list of countries and dependencies by population</b>. It includes <a href="/wiki/Sovereign_state" title="Sovereign state">sovereign states</a>, inhabited <a href="/wiki/Dependent_territory" title="Dependent territory">dependent territories</a> and, in some cases, <a href="/wiki/Country#Sovereignty" title="Country">constituent countries</a> of sovereign states, with inclusion within the list being primarily based on the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/ISO" title="ISO">ISO</a> standard <a href="/wiki/ISO_3166-1" title="ISO 3166-1">ISO 3166-1</a>. For instance, the <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a> is considered as a single entity, while the constituent countries of the <a href="/wiki/Kingdom_of_the_Netherlands" title="Kingdom of the Netherlands">Kingdom of the Netherlands</a> are considered separately. In addition, this list includes certain <a href="/wiki/List_of_states_with_limited_recognition" title="List of states with limited recognition">states with limited recognition</a> not found in ISO 3166-1. Also given in percent is each country's population compared with the <a href="/wiki/World_population" title="World population">world population</a>, which the <a href="/wiki/United_Nations" title="United Nations">United Nations</a> estimates at 7.88 billion today.
</p>
<div aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading" class="toc" id="toc" role="navigation"><input class="toctogglecheckbox" id="toctogglecheckbox" role="button" style="display:none" type="checkbox"/><div class="toctitle" dir="ltr" lang="en"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Method">Method</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=List_of_countries_and_dependencies_by_population&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Method">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" role="note">See also: <a href="/wiki/List_of_countries_and_dependencies_by_population_density" title="List of countries and dependencies by population density">List of countries and dependencies by population density</a> and <a href="/wiki/List_of_regional_organizations_by_population" title="List of regional organizations by population">List of regional organizations by population</a></div>
<p>Figures used in this chart are based on the most up to date <a href="/wiki/Population_projection" title="Population projection">estimate or projections</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-1"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup> by the national <a href="/wiki/Census" title="Census">census</a> authority where available, and are usually rounded off.
</p><p>Where updated national data are not available, figures are based on the projections for 2021 by the Population Division of the <a href="/wiki/United_Nations_Department_of_Economic_and_Social_Affairs" title="United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs">United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-unpop_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-unpop-2">[2]</a></sup>
</p><p>Because the compiled figures are not collected at the same time in every country, or at the same level of <a href="/wiki/Statistics" title="Statistics">accuracy</a>, the resulting numerical comparisons may create misleading conclusions. Furthermore, the addition of figures from all countries may not equal the world total.
</p><p>Areas that form integral parts of sovereign states, such as the <a href="/wiki/Countries_of_the_United_Kingdom" title="Countries of the United Kingdom">countries of the United Kingdom</a>, are counted as part of the sovereign states concerned. Not included are other entities, such as the <a href="/wiki/European_Union" title="European Union">European Union</a>,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[a]</a></sup> that are not sovereign states, and independent territories that do not have permanent populations, such as <a href="/wiki/Territorial_claims_in_Antarctica" title="Territorial claims in Antarctica">various countries' claims</a> to <a href="/wiki/Antarctica" title="Antarctica">Antarctica</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sovereign_states_and_dependencies_by_population">Sovereign states and dependencies by population</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=List_of_countries_and_dependencies_by_population&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Sovereign states and dependencies by population">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Note: A number rank is assigned to the 193 <a href="/wiki/Member_states_of_the_United_Nations" title="Member states of the United Nations">member states of the United Nations</a> and the two <a href="/wiki/United_Nations_General_Assembly_observers#Present_non-member_observers" title="United Nations General Assembly observers">observer states to the United Nations General Assembly</a>. Dependent territories and constituent countries that are parts of sovereign states are not assigned a numbered rank. In addition, sovereign states with limited recognition are included, but not assigned a number rank.
</p>

<li id="cite_note-159"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-159">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Kosovo is the subject of a territorial dispute between the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Republic_of_Kosovo" title="Republic of Kosovo">Republic of Kosovo</a> and the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Republic_of_Serbia" title="Republic of Serbia">Republic of Serbia</a>. The Republic of Kosovo <a href="/wiki/2008_Kosovo_declaration_of_independence" title="2008 Kosovo declaration of independence">unilaterally declared independence</a> on 17 February 2008. <a href="/wiki/Kosovo%E2%80%93Serbia_relations" title="KosovoSerbia relations">Serbia continues to claim</a> it as part of its <a href="/wiki/Autonomous_Province_of_Kosovo_and_Metohija" title="Autonomous Province of Kosovo and Metohija">own sovereign territory</a>. The two governments <a href="/wiki/Belgrade%E2%80%93Pristina_negotiations" title="BelgradePristina negotiations">began to normalise relations</a> in 2013, as part of the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/2013_Brussels_Agreement" title="2013 Brussels Agreement">2013 Brussels Agreement</a>. Kosovo is currently <i>(this note self-updates)</i> recognized as an independent state by <a href="/wiki/International_recognition_of_Kosovo" title="International recognition of Kosovo">98</a> out of the 193 <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/United_Nations_member_states" title="United Nations member states">United Nations member states</a>. In total, <a href="/wiki/International_recognition_of_Kosovo" title="International recognition of Kosovo">113</a> UN member states recognized Kosovo at some point, of which <a href="/wiki/International_recognition_of_Kosovo" title="International recognition of Kosovo">15</a> later withdrew their recognition.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-169"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-169">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Excluding <a href="/wiki/Northern_Cyprus" title="Northern Cyprus">Northern Cyprus</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-177"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-177">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Administration is split between <a href="/wiki/Morocco" title="Morocco">Morocco</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Sahrawi_Arab_Democratic_Republic" title="Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic">Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic</a>, both of which claim the entire territory.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-181"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-181">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>De facto</i> independent, <i>de jure</i> part of <a href="/wiki/Moldova" title="Moldova">Moldova</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-187"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-187">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>De facto</i> independent, <i>de jure</i> part of <a href="/wiki/Cyprus" title="Cyprus">Cyprus</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-190"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-190">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Abkhazia" title="Abkhazia">Abkhazia</a> is the subject of a territorial dispute between the <a href="/wiki/Abkhazia" title="Abkhazia">Republic of Abkhazia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Georgia_(country)" title="Georgia (country)">Georgia</a>. The Republic of Abkhazia unilaterally declared independence on 23 July 1992, but Georgia continues to claim it as part of its <a href="/wiki/Government_of_the_Autonomous_Republic_of_Abkhazia" title="Government of the Autonomous Republic of Abkhazia">own sovereign territory</a> and designates it as a <a href="/wiki/Occupied_territories_of_Georgia" title="Occupied territories of Georgia">territory occupied</a> by <a href="/wiki/Russia" title="Russia">Russia</a>. Abkhazia has received formal recognition as an independent state from <a href="/wiki/International_recognition_of_Abkhazia_and_South_Ossetia" title="International recognition of Abkhazia and South Ossetia">7</a> out of 193 <a href="/wiki/United_Nations" title="United Nations">United Nations</a> <a href="/wiki/Member_states_of_the_United_Nations" title="Member states of the United Nations">member states</a>, 1 of which has subsequently withdrawn its recognition.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-195"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-195">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>De facto</i> independent, <i>de jure</i> part of <a href="/wiki/Azerbaijan" title="Azerbaijan">Azerbaijan</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-207"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-207">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/South_Ossetia" title="South Ossetia">South Ossetia</a>'s status is disputed. It  considers itself to be an independent state, but this is recognised by <a href="/wiki/International_recognition_of_Abkhazia_and_South_Ossetia#States_formally_recognising_Abkhazia_or_South_Ossetia_as_independent" title="International recognition of Abkhazia and South Ossetia">only a  few other countries</a>. The <a href="/wiki/Georgia_(country)" title="Georgia (country)">Georgian</a> government and most of the  world's other states consider South Ossetia <i><a href="/wiki/De_jure" title="De jure">de jure</a></i>  a part of Georgia's territory.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-219"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-219">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The total population of 825 consisted of 453 residents and 372 nonresident citizens.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>

Creating Initial Dataframe¶

By using soup and pandas we extracted the table from wikipedia page which contains all the information that we are going to use in our Dataframe.

In [6]:
blank_list = []
for i in soup.find('tbody').select('tr'):
    try:
        text = i.text.split('\n')
        text.remove('')
        blank_list.append(text)
    except:
        pass
In [7]:
for i in blank_list:
    i.remove('')
df = pd.DataFrame(blank_list[:-1])
df.columns = df.loc[0,:]
df.dropna(axis=1,inplace=True)
df.drop(0,axis=0,inplace=True)
#df.drop('Rank',axis=1,inplace=True)

Data Cleaning¶

We found that there are some texts which need to be cleaned for the proper data analysis. Here, we are removing the extra characters from the dataframe that we have formed.

In [9]:
df['Country or dependent territory'] = [i[:-5].replace('','') if i[-3]=='[' else i.replace('','') for i in df['Country or dependent territory']]
df['Source (official or United Nations)'] = [i[:i.find('[')] for i in df['Source (official or United Nations)']]
In [10]:

Putting Flag Images:¶

  • Finally we are trying to extract the links from the same website to add the flag images of the countries to our dataframe.
In [11]:
first_table = soup.find_all(class_ = 'wikitable')[0]
table_img = first_table.find_all('img')
In [12]:
df['flags'] = ["https:"+i['src'].strip() for i in table_img]
df
